text.__SUMMARY__: Scleria robinsoniana is a plant in the nutrush genus Scleria of the sedge family Cyperaceae.
text.Distribution and habitat:
Scleria robinsoniana grows naturally in Guinea, Sierra Leone and the Central African Republic. Its habitat is seasonally wet stony areas from sea-level to 1,200 metres (4,000 ft) altitude.
